<subSubSection id="9F2013DF31335F172AB1314F624E25E4" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8D93654FE0E75BCF76B287E5C14E7A04" pageId="5" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName id="40BE68D1340E6DA6E9722B5E9E62469C" class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="hemichrysa" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
Skottsb., Kongl. Svenska Vetenskapsakad. Handl. ser. 3, 14(2): 46. 1934.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9806EBFAA4B6953E943C0B6C4D6E9C42" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" type="note">
<paragraph id="C8A70188079D7575F028CCB9CCE1AE9C" pageId="5" pageNumber="110">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B55EEC4B675BD85EB1EB33A5D15C0077" pageId="5" pageNumber="110">
Flowers with a short perianth tube (0.2-1.1 mm); anthers dorsifixed, versatile; ovary uni- (
<taxonomicName id="CF12F910626068DFB450A106EDFF583D" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Desmoneuron" species="hemichrysa" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Desmoneuron</taxonomicName>
) or trilocular (
<taxonomicName id="DD958ADF02C1D435CE7827B748362774" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Isoneuron" species="hemichrysa" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Isoneuron</taxonomicName>
); seeds obovoid, obovoid-reniform, or turbinate-polygonal; funicle ribbed, mucilaginous funicular hairs well developed that surround but do not adhere to the seed; Type: 
<taxonomicName id="567001FAB9F1556988A6E2A3A648DBA8" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia trinervia" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trinervia">
<emphasis id="CFA88FED193679B499F67B5CC20EEB42" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="110">Astelia trinervia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kirk, designated here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C8D1C49A8E70EEC17A91E4DFDBFB22C9" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="C0571D6A7E02454484543A6476A46A20" pageId="5" pageNumber="110">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE23D19A2C4C61368B11B0B0D43EF8DE" pageId="5" pageNumber="110">
Phylogenetic analyses indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="FDB7DDAAA904F3864A1B730815B93589" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="trinervia" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
, as circumscribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="8944320E4C36629A395B36A25ECCCBDD" author="Skottsberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" pagination="1 - 128" refId="B28" refString="Skottsberg, C, 1934. Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander. Kungliga Svenska Vetensaps-Akademiens Handlingar 14 (2): 1 - 128" title="Studies in the genus Astelia Banks et Solander." volume="14" year="1934">Skottsberg (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, is polyphyletic (Birch unpublished PhD thesis 2011, 
<bibRefCitation id="D98AE2CE8C0B06FD1C06215FA7CC5F12" author="Birch, JL" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="117" pagination="102 - 115" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" refId="B2" refString="Birch, JL, Keeley, SC, Morden, CW, 2012. Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s.l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 102 - 115, DOI: 10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" title="Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s. l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" volume="65" year="2012">Birch et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="BAF67FC35283CA126089058058BF046B" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="trinervia" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
is revised to include 
<taxonomicName id="2126D403125076B7326E90D2E6E7AE2D" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Isoneuron" species="trinervia" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Isoneuron</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="55CD0774B29EBEBE130DEC3BB61A4EC9" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Desmoneuron" species="trinervia" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Desmoneuron</taxonomicName>
, which form a clade. But, as 
<taxonomicName id="DA1058CD807373ECE0C043BD2B4DD126" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Periastelia" species="trinervia" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Periastelia</taxonomicName>
, is placed in a different clade, it is excluded from 
<taxonomicName id="9EAC14A02FCEFFEBC00892B362CB3767" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="trinervia" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
